"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A young Moabite widow, who, because of her selfless devotion to her mother-in-law Naomi, and to Naomi's God, gained a husband and a child, a place in Jewish history and became the great-grandmother of David and an ancestor of Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>Ruth faces the problems of widowhood</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:3-Ruth1:5\">RUT 1:3–1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:6-Ruth1:13\">RUT 1:6–1:13</a></p>\n<h2>Ruth commits herself to Naomi</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:16-Ruth1:17\">RUT 1:16–1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:18\">RUT 1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:22\">RUT 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:11\">RUT 2:11</a></p>\n<h2>Ruth and Boaz</h2>\n<h3>Boaz allows Ruth to glean in his fields</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:8-Ruth2:9\">RUT 2:8–2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:14-Ruth2:23\">RUT 2:14–2:23</a></p>\n<h3>Ruth asks Boaz to be her ``kinsman-redeemer''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth3:9\">RUT 3:9</a></strong> <em>The kinsman-redeemer was the closest male relative who had responsibility to marry a widow within the family and thereby protect the interests of needy members of the extended family.</em></p>\n<h3>Boaz negotiates with a nearer relative of Ruth's</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:1-Ruth4:8\">RUT 4:1–4:8</a></p>\n<h3>Boaz marries Ruth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:9-Ruth4:10\">RUT 4:9–4:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:11-Ruth4:13\">RUT 4:11–4:13</a></p>\n<h3>She has a son who is presented to Naomi</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:13\">RUT 4:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:17\">RUT 4:17</a></p>\n<h2>Ruth is included in the genealogy of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:5-Matt1:6\">MAT 1:5–1:6</a></strong></p>",
